Problem Statement

You are given a graph with n nodes, initially disconnected (zero edges).
Each node has a value written on it such that the i-th node has the value i.
A range [l, r] is "covered" in a set s if for each i from l to r, i appears in s.
The "beauty" of a set s is defined as the minimum number of covered ranges such that each element of s belongs to at least one of these ranges. 
For example: beauty({1, 2, 4, 5, 8, 11}) = 4 (the ranges are [1, 2], [4, 5], [8], and [11]).

You have to process q queries of two types:
Type 1 - (1, u, v): Add an edge between u and v.
Type 2 - (2, u, 0): Find the beauty (number of covered ranges) in the connected component of u.

Find the sum of answers to all Type 2 queries.

Constraints
1 <= n <= 10^5
1 <= q <= 10^5
t = 3 (number of columns in queries)
0 <= queries[i][j] <= n

